AI response: I have implemented the binary target variable construction. The labelling function inspects each row's transaction direction and realized alpha: a Purchase with alpha exceeding +5% receives label 1 because it indicates the senator entered a position just before a statistically significant market-beating move; a Sale with alpha below −5% similarly receives label 1. Rows with missing alpha are conservatively assigned 0. The threshold of 5% is deliberately conservative — it corresponds to roughly one standard deviation of monthly S&P 500 returns, so random occurrence is unlikely. Crucially, the alpha column is used only to construct this label and is explicitly excluded from the feature matrix used to train all downstream models, preventing any form of target leakage.

